<br>
First, my favorite vampire not in print, is Nicholas Knight played by Geraint Wyn Davies, from the Canadian TV show, Forever Knight.  From the same show, Lucien LaCroix, played by Nigel Bennett, was hot too.<br>
<br>
As for my favorite vampire in print, it would have to be Lestat.<br>
A bit of useless trivia for those who are interested, I heard Anne Rice, in an interview, saying that when she first conceived the character Lestat, the actor she had in mind was Rutger Hauer, but by the time the movie was made, he was considered to be too old for the part.  Personally, I think Rutger Hauer would have made a more convincing Lestat, old or not (besides, older men are sexy), but the movie wasn't too bad, despite Tom Cruise being in it.  (Is it just me, or is anyone else sick of this guy?)<br>
<br>
Bye for now,<br>
<br>
Bonnie <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/emoticons_classic/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bunexplainedmysteries.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chargerfan1>Chargerfan1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/3/02 3:30:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm76.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=59>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Dracula/Vampire of all time???</span><hr size=1> Rutger Hauer is one of my favorite actors.  He was sinister in &quot;the Hitcher&quot;.  <br>
<br>
As far as Blade/Blade II are concerned, they are comic book adaptations and should be evaluated as such.  Perhaps a vampire purist would not like the martial arts aspect of it, so the comparison isn't really fair.  Blade is a Marvel character.  Anyway, I thought that they were entertaining films.    <br>
<br>
The Lugosi Dracula film has a special place for me, but it's not one of my favorites.  I liked 'Vampyr' by Dreyer much better.  For more recent vampires, Christorpher Lee in 'The Horror of Dracula&quot; and &quot;Taste the Blood of Dracula&quot; were pretty good.  I really liked the 1979 version of Dracula, with Frank Langella.  I thought it a well made film with excellent acting and sets.  <br>
<br>
Coppolla's version was aptly nicknamed at the time as &quot;MTV's Dracula&quot;.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :-) --><img src=http://web.ukonline.co.uk/unexplained.m/smile/3dsm.gif ALT=":-)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
